# NadBurn — frontend environment variables
#
# These are read at build time by Vite. Anything prefixed with VITE_ is
# bundled into the client JS, so do NOT put server-only secrets here.

# ----- Backend api-server URL (required for production deploy) -----------
#
# When the frontend is deployed to Vercel (nadburn.xyz) and the api-server
# is deployed to Replit Deployments, the frontend must call the api-server
# with an absolute URL. Otherwise relative `/api/*` calls land on Vercel,
# which has no api routes and returns its own 404 page (the violet
# "NOT_FOUND iad1::…" blob users see in the recovery list).
#
# Set this on the Vercel project (Project Settings → Environment Variables)
# to the published Replit api-server URL, no trailing slash:
#
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL="https://nadburn-api.replit.app"
#
# Leave UNSET in the Replit dev preview — the shared port-80 proxy already
# routes `/api/*` to the local api-server, and absolute URLs would only
# add a network hop. Same for any environment where frontend + api are
# served from the same origin.

# ----- Mainnet hardening (required for production deploy) ----------------

# Dedicated Ethereum mainnet RPC (Alchemy, Infura, QuickNode, Ankr, etc.).
# The public fallback works for dev but will rate-limit and time out under
# real traffic. Set this before going to mainnet.
# VITE_MAINNET_RPC_URL="https://eth-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_KEY"

# Optional: dedicated Monad mainnet RPC. The default is dRPC's free public
# endpoint. For production traffic prefer Alchemy / QuickNode / Chainstack.
# VITE_MONAD_MAINNET_RPC_URL="https://monad-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_KEY"

# Optional: dedicated Monad testnet RPC. The default is the public endpoint.
# VITE_MONAD_RPC_URL="https://testnet-rpc.monad.xyz"

# WalletConnect project ID (https://cloud.walletconnect.com). Without this,
# only injected/MetaMask/Coinbase wallets show up. Mobile users need this.
# VITE_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID="abcdef0123456789..."

# ----- Recovery fee --------------------------------------------------------

# Address that receives the recovery service fee. Defaults to the team
# treasury baked into constants.ts.
# VITE_FEE_RECIPIENT="0xYourTreasuryAddress"

# Mainnet recovery batch fee in wei. Defaults to 0 (no fee on mainnet).
# Example: 0.005 ETH → 5000000000000000
# VITE_MAINNET_RECOVERY_FEE_WEI="5000000000000000"

# ----- API server secrets (set in api-server, NOT here) ------------------
#
# Recovery on V4-only chains (Monad mainnet, chain 143) routes through
# Uniswap's Trading API via our backend proxy. The API key lives on the
# api-server side as a Replit secret named:
#
#   UNISWAP_TRADING_API_KEY
#
# Get a key at https://hub.uniswap.org. For local dev you can use the
# playground key from https://api-docs.uniswap.org. Without the key set,
# recovery on chain 143 shows a configuration banner; burn still works.
#
# Auto-detect on Monad mainnet (chain 143) routes through Blockvision's
# hosted indexer. Sign up at https://blockvision.org for a free API key
# and store it on the api-server side as a Replit secret named:
#
#   BLOCKVISION_API_KEY
#
# Without this key set, auto-detect on Monad mainnet returns a friendly
# "configure auto-detect" message and the user can still paste contract
# addresses manually. Ethereum + Monad testnet auto-detect work without
# this key (they use public Blockscout endpoints).
